{
  "doc_id": "34716",
  "text": "Besides its potential function as a biomarker for schizophrenia, CRP is also synthesized by hepatocytes under the regulatory control of IL-6, released by macrophages and adipocytes [CITATION_1] . Elevated IL-6 levels have also been linked to schizophrenia [CITATION_2] and were especially related to negative symptoms [CITATION_3] . Furthermore, IL-6 was shown to be increased prior to the onset of schizophrenia [CITATION_4] .",
